    "synopsis": "The death of a rich and ancient Rogue Trader brings his Charter of Trade — a relic literally signed by the Emperor — to Hydraphur, where Calpurnia must see Hoyyon Phrax's will carried out under Imperial law. Rival heirs decide that due process be damned, and the administrators of a will must take up arms on the side of legal process — while ambitious clerics of the Ecclesiarchy, drawn by the relic, open a second front. The procedural shades into court-intrigue.",
